	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 29th 1:34 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, my main is an untwinked, lvl 23 rogue on Saryrn Server, so I can't comment on higher end gear and skills. However, I can tell you that I successfully solo-ed my way up to lvl 21, and only recently got into groups just to see what it was like ... so this talk about how rogues can't solo is absurd. I think I could easily continue solo-ing up into my 30s. And this talk about letting us bandage more or whatever, forget that! It's my impression that as it is we have no level cap when it comes to dual wield (that's sweet). Maybe remove the cap for parry as well. But, if you really want to help a rogue, allow them to &quot;con&quot; NPCs, mobs and merchants to raise faction temporarily (when buying and selling for example). THAT would rock! And totally fit with being a rogue.<br><br>As for grouping though, any group that does not want a rogue, obviously doesn't know what a rogue brings to the table. Why do parties group? Two reasons: for xp and loot. We can help with the xp by dealing massive damage in the form of a backstab and almost flawless dual wield. Also, if you're tank gets tired or hurting, a good backstab while he steps away will pull the mob to you. This is very appreciated by those tanks. Not to mention, I pull with my rogue and tank myself every now and then to give the big tanks a rest. We can take it, and the big tanks love us for it. If you get hurt, pull back, the mob will aggro the other guy, and you hide!<br><br>As for loot, we can almost double the loot. How's that you say? Max out your pickpocket skill, then during the fight (with the use of hot keys) pick the pocket of the mob (yes, it only works for humanoid mobs). If you get coin, it does not take away from what the mob was going to drop anyway, and if you get an item (ooh! a page from some book!) let everyone know and offer to give it up (it's like 5gp anyway). OK, if it is a jade, keep it for yourself :P Now, here's the good part though. After a while of picking pockets, you will have picked a good amount of gold and platinum (I love picking platinum) and TONS of silver and copper. I always split the silver and copper with the party. It not only reduces my weight, but everyone in the party is excited to get &quot;free&quot; coin. What do I care if I lose 200sp, when I picked 5pp?!<br><br>And lastly, poison. I love poison. I am a huge fan of poison. I never really was able to take an even con until I used poison. But, yes, it can be pricey. VERY pricey. And I think that needs to be fixed. However, until that time, here's what I do. The only new skills to a rogue in the 20s are (I believe) instill doubt (love it) and riposte (can't wait). Since these skills get better with use anyway, don't waste your points... put all your practice points in making and applying poison. At the same time, become a Master Potter (really not that hard or expensive) to cut the costs of those poison vials. Then only make the basic poisons. I stick with asp and spider poisons. Easy to farm and/or buy from newbies and it’s amazing how much these basic poisons can help you. Using either one I can take an even con every time, with hp to spare. And, since I am picking pockets during the fight anyway, I tend to get all my money back I just spent. Not to mention, it’s just fun to say in a group “Save the mana, I’ll weaken this one”… or even better “Gee, 75 point backstab plus 100 points due to poison … all in 3 seconds.”<br><br>I hope this rant helps people. Don’t forget, be creative…. And have fun always!<br><br>Restyn<br>Rogue of Saryrn Server<br>23 Seasons<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Restyn<br>Rogue of Saryrn Server<br>32 Seasons</td></tr>
