	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ack! You all know I just love debates, especially if they're almost pointless like this one. If he wants to try soloing, let him. Personally, I could still solo up until 29, but I had to make sure I kept bandages on me. I haven't done any combat at 30 yet, and besides that I lost all my equipment, but I would tend to think that riposte, damage bonuses, disease discipline, and my burning rapier starting to proc will more than offset the increased difficulty at a higher level. In other words, I hope that soloing at 30 will be easier than it was at 29.<br><br>Anyway, I haven't read nearly all of everyone's arguments yet; I'm way too tired. I just want to point out one thing that no one (at least I think no one) has pointed out correctly. Duel wield is capped at 6*(lvl+1). Slip was close, but no cigar. Oh and I don't know if anyone pointed this out, but pick pocket DOES take away from the drop table. When you only pick at most 1 or 2pp from a mob, I know it's hard to tell, but when you get over 6pp several times in a night off mobs that usually carry only 5-7pp, you can tell there's not much left.<br><br>Level 24 and you're only BSing for 75? Sounds like you're still using a walrus tooth. Or maybe you're one of those wimpy elves (any kind). J/K Restyn and any offended elves, this post is meant only as constructive criticism.<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 32nd Dwarf Rogue<br>Lords of Belterra<br>Xegony</td></tr>
