	   <tr><td colspan=2>I completely agree with Slipskin in debunking the majority of your statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;I can remember the time when I would've agreed with everything you said Restyn, but like you, after discussion and experience I learned the truth.<br><br>1) You could probably solo to 40th if you wanted but the only mobs you'll end up fighting will be light blue and it'll take FOREVER to gain levels.  As you solo, you effectively lose your backstab.  Don't believe for an instant that Instill Doubt or even Fear-based poisons are going to help you soloing.<br><br>2) PPing in a group does steal from the group. There was a rumor that each mob had two loot tables... one for the group and one for the rogue.  As much as I wanted to believe that was true, it's really not.  Once you gain sufficient levels, go to Rathe Mountains where the hill giants can carry up to 40 plats.  Get in a group and pick pockets as much as possible.  You'll notice that you'll pick 10-30 plats per battle and the HGs will have little left to give to the group at the end of the battle.  Trust me on this one.<br><br>3) At your lvl, passing aggro between you and the Main Tank is a viable strategy when you are short on healers in your group.  You share the pain and, therefore, reduce downtime between pulls.  However, as you hit 30+, it is actually much more effective to keep the aggro on the Tank (they'll have MUCH more hit points than you and a MUCH better AC).  Any rogue that keeps aggro at higher levels is a dead rogue.<br><br>4) Poisons are fun.  But, you'll find that it becomes VERY expensive to buy vials and ingredients.  Most ingredients are dropped from mobs, but it's not really efficient to go hunting mobs for those drops.  Also, unless you practice a whole lot more than you advance in levels, you end up making poisons that are consistantly resisted by the mobs that you are fighting.  I gave up poisons at 42nd lvl because the Tier Two poisons that I could make were not working against the mobs I was fighting.  And, I didn't wanna waste thousands of plats getting my skill up over 150.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Fluxus<br>Officer of Forbidden Legion<br>Tarew Marr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160</a></td></tr>
