	   <tr><td colspan=2>Seriously, I like some of the ideas, but for the most part, a lot of you lower level Rogues will be astounded when you get into your 40s.<br><br>At this level, Soloing even light blue cons will be a fight for your life.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless you get really lucky with Instill Doubt, have a Locustlure, and a good ammount of other items (SBD maybe for chasing).<br><br>Also at this level, the only things you'll be able to farm easily solo are mobs no higher than level 20ish.  The Rogue becomes a powerful group class, but you won't get anywhere trying to solo.  I've been in DL for a good long time now, and even the lower level Drolvargs can put a beating to me.  <br><br>I still haven't even tried poisons yet, due to the high cost, but I have collected poison items throughout my career, including asp/snake poison sacs, sulfur, embalming dust, mortar, etc.  It's just more rewarding to save your cash and buy gear.  Hopefully VI will fix poisons<br>&nbsp;<br>-----------------------<br>Rogues do it from behind.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276</a> <br>Tyrlinoth Arkonnen - The Nameless</td></tr>
