	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just to give you a taste of what is to come with rogues tanking :(<br><br>Last night my level 40 rogue and a 38 druid were hunting in Rathe Mts.&nbsp;&nbsp;We pulled a Hill Giant and we had him down to half hits. Druid was about half mana from healing me constantly.  I used Snake Venom poison (level 1 DOT).  Then a Lizardman Warrior decided to jump the Druid.  Druid keeps getting interrupted and my HP drains away like a keg at a frat party.  I run (SoW in effect).  Druid runs.  Another group snags the HG and saves our butts.<br><br>We go to a more isolated spot and start doing Cyclopses.  Still, they con light and dark blue but I know they're a few levels lower than HG's.  I pull one. Druid heals and damage shields me.  I tell the Druid to snare the dude.  I start hitting Instill Doubt.  About the third try it catches and the Cyclopse is running like a panicked child.  But the druid forgot to snare so it was real tough keeping up and getting in the backstabs.  We finally get the system down right and drop 4 cyclopses and a pesky undead giant skeleton in about 20 minutes.  If it wasn't for Instill Doubt the druid would have been OOM just from casting heal spells and we would have been heading for the zone - because of a Cyclops!<br><br>Moral of story:  Rogues just don't have the HP to tank.  Remember that before you try to solo your rogue.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
